PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (Schedule No. 938) establishing Maximum Residue Limits for fluazifop-butyl (a selective postemergence herbicide used in the control of a wide range of annual and perennial grasses in broadleaf crops) in mustard at 0.3 ppm, and in milk at 0.01 ppm because of the possible feeding of treated forage or crops to livestock.

Attachments
precis:
Amendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (Schedule No. 938) establishing
Maximum Residue Limits for fluazifop-butyl (a selective postemergence
herbicide used in the control of a wide range of annual and perennial
grasses in broadleaf crops) in mustard at 0.3 ppm, and in milk at 0.01 ppm
because of the possible feeding of treated forage or crops to livestock.
